          <avActivityHighlights>Individual avalanche prone locations are to be found on wind-loaded slopes at elevated altitudes.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>In some localities 5 to 10 cm of snow fell yesterday above approximately 1700 m. As a consequence of new snow and wind from northeasterly directions, rather small wind slabs formed. These can in some places be released, in particular by large loads. In particular on wind-loaded slopes the avalanches can be released in the various wind slab layers and reach medium size.</avActivityComment>
